<def f='linux-4.18.y/kernel/irq/irqdesc.c' l='936' ll='944' type='unsigned int kstat_irqs_usr(unsigned int irq)'/>
<doc f='linux-4.18.y/kernel/irq/irqdesc.c' l='927'>/**
 * kstat_irqs_usr - Get the statistics for an interrupt
 * @irq:	The interrupt number
 *
 * Returns the sum of interrupt counts on all cpus since boot for
 * @irq. Contrary to kstat_irqs() this can be called from any
 * preemptible context. It&apos;s protected against concurrent removal of
 * an interrupt descriptor when sparse irqs are enabled.
 */</doc>
